# Environment Variables Setup

Copy this to your `.env.local` file and fill in your credentials.

## Google AdSense (Optional)
```bash
# Google AdSense Configuration
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_CLIENT=ca-pub-XXXXXXXXXXXXXXXXX
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_SLOT_BANNER=XXXXXXXXXX
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_SLOT_INTERSTITIAL=XXXXXXXXXX
# NEXT_PUBLIC_ADSENSE_VERIFICATION=XXXXXXXXXX
```

## PayPal Payment Processing (Required for Premium)
```bash
# PayPal Configuration
# Get these from: https://developer.sandbox.paypal.com/dashboard

# Public Client ID (visible to browser)
NEXT_PUBLIC_PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID=YourPayPalClientIdHere

# Secret Key (backend only - NEVER commit this)
PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET=YourPayPalClientSecretHere
```

## Supabase (Already configured)
```bash
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL=your_supabase_url
NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your_supabase_key
```

---

## Getting PayPal Credentials (Sandbox - for testing)

1. Go to [developer.sandbox.paypal.com](https://developer.sandbox.paypal.com)
2. Sign in with your PayPal account (create one if needed)
3. Go to **Apps & Credentials**
4. Create a new **Business** app
5. Copy the **Client ID** → `NEXT_PUBLIC_PAYPAL_CLIENT_ID`
6. Click **Show** next to **Secret** → `PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET`

## Getting PayPal Credentials (Production - for real money)

1. Go to [paypal.com/business](https://www.paypal.com/business)
2. Set up a business account
3. Go to **Account Settings** → **API Signature**
4. Use your live **Client ID** and **Secret**

---

## Important Security Notes

✅ **DO commit:**
- `.env.local` template with example values
- `NEXT_PUBLIC_*` variables (these are public)

❌ **NEVER commit:**
- `PAYPAL_CLIENT_SECRET` (backend only!)
- Actual API keys or credentials
- `.env.local` file itself

Add to `.gitignore`:
```bash
.env.local
.env.production.local
.env.*.local
```
